      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "a2d03740f755c035",
      "text": "And medium, function, encoding, and symbiosis are some of the criteria that we normally reserve for societal operating systems, such as functional systems. One method of analyzing a presumed functional system is to test through this set of criteria in each case. The page: [[Medium and Symbiotic Mechanism]], for example, was created in the context of such an analysis of the politics of the society. Another page: [[Function and Operation]] addresses the question: how does the specificity of politics differ from other social communication by a particular function? Followed by the page: [[Code and Reference]] which looks at the same question in regard to a particular encoding."
